  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they handed me a large envelope with the passports of my parents and my sister, and a Gestapo report headed-- Gestapo, Gestapo letterhead-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in very thorough-- typically German thorough format, telling of the arrest of the-- of the married couple leaving, who were trying to escape from Germany and blah, blah, blah, and were sent, were arrested-- and placed under arrest and sent to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 70
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's the first word I heard-- the first time I heard the word 'Auschwitz' in, in the-- in this whole matter.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because, as I say, nobody-- it came [LAUGHS] indeed from-- the government source for anything is the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Nothing has been heard from them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nothing has been heard from my sister or about my sister or about them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My-- the only thing I know about my sister's fate is that she was apparently sent to Riga in Latvia, which had a whole history of ghettoization and then ghetto extermination and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] as the receiving locale for deported German Jews and Austrian Jews, and-- from various sources, mainly German, though, mainly from Berlin, it seems.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Whether she got there via Poland, where she might have-- she might have spent some time in a camp, in Lublin or not, it doesn't matter.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She ended up in Riga.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there has been no word.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I have spent a great many years and a great many efforts in trying to trace her, particularly, because she is the-- was the most likely to have-- to have maybe survived in some form or other.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I was interested to find out that there is an association in America of survivors of the Riga Ghetto, enough of them to actually form an association.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I've been in touch with them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I've advertised.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
